    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.5041/33.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No possibility of agreement in stevedore strike; fifteen-day truce ends to-morrow
                    at midnight. Stevedore and lightermen announce that they will then go on strike,
                    with strong possibility of general strike in Habana and other cities. In present
                    crisis stoppage of foodstuffs and customs receipts would have serious effect.
                    Suggest advisability of sending ships with marines to Key West, whence they
                    could be quickly summoned in the event of trouble.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
